Former University of Nairobi professor Tumbo Oeri has died from a suspected heart attack. Oeri's nephew, Kitutu Chache South MP Richard Onyonka, said he collapsed in his house at about 4 am on Wednesday. He was pronounced dead at the hospital to which he was taken. Oeri served as UoN's Chiromo campus principal and often appeared on KTN News as a panelist. Click here for the latest political news  More to follow